The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 25: The company law board today issued notices to West Bengal Industrial Development Corp, IOC and Haldia Petrochemicals Ltd chairman on an application by The Chatterjee Group, seeking recall of the board?s interim order on allotment of shares to Indian Oil. The CLB had reserved its order on August 23 on the application filed by TCG. The board said it was not inclined to pass any order at this stage and sought a reply from IOC, WBIDC and HPL chairman saying the fresh application to recall the interim order on the issue would be heard with the main application on September 27. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 25: The Reserve Bank today specified stringent norms to consider applications by resident Indians to transfer securities to persons residing outside the country as a gift.

 Mumbai, Aug. 25: Pantaloon Retail (India) Ltd has announced a rights issue in the ratio of 1:5. The issue will be priced at Rs 500 per share, totalling Rs 224 crore.

 Mumbai, Aug. 25: Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd (HDFC) today launched a $500-million zero coupon foreign currency convertible bond.

 Mumbai, Aug. 25: Novell has acquired total control of the Indian joint venture, Onward Novell.




